01:00.575 --> 01:01.818
Goddamn.

01:01.968 --> 01:03.071
More lightning.

01:04.596 --> 01:06.326
Spark a few more fires.

01:06.590 --> 01:08.741
I wish it would rain
with some of these storms.

01:11.849 --> 01:12.983
Shit, look!

01:20.748 --> 01:21.959
Is he alright?

01:22.936 --> 01:23.839
Jesus!

01:24.558 --> 01:26.210
What's on your face? Those aren't burns.

01:26.360 --> 01:27.913
What's wrong with your face?

01:44.349 --> 01:45.963
Hey, you talk to immigration?

01:46.113 --> 01:49.728
Yes. Elvia is back in Mexico
with her grandmother and cousins.

01:51.235 --> 01:53.116
That's what she wanted, right?

01:53.317 --> 01:54.997
That's all she had left.

01:58.524 --> 02:00.781
You still feel like hitting something?

02:05.934 --> 02:06.937
Yeah.

02:07.388 --> 02:10.128
You know, sometimes
I feel like the world is just...

02:10.312 --> 02:12.498
- pushing me into a corner.
- I hear that.

02:13.581 --> 02:16.452
Feel like ya gotta do
whatever ya gotta do to get out of it.

02:16.765 --> 02:17.768
Yeah.

02:18.702 --> 02:21.604
But assaulting a federal officer's not
the best way to go about it.

02:21.987 --> 02:23.554
I know that.

02:24.218 --> 02:25.146
Hey.

02:25.640 --> 02:27.114
You want the name of my therapist?

02:42.355 --> 02:43.353
Doctor Lowen?

02:43.503 --> 02:44.580
Right over there.

02:44.732 --> 02:45.821
Doctor Lowen?

02:46.534 --> 02:48.618
David Sandström. Carlos Serrano.

02:48.768 --> 02:50.834
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you. Alex.

02:50.984 --> 02:52.055
Thanks for coming.

02:52.205 --> 02:55.724
Your alert to the CDC got our attention,
so we take a first-hand look.

02:55.874 --> 02:58.183
Well normally, I'm dealing with
smoke inhalation,

02:58.339 --> 03:00.021
fatigue, dehydration, but this?

03:00.171 --> 03:02.211
- I don't know what to do.
- Can I have a look?

03:02.362 --> 03:04.644
- Yeah, please. Here.
- Thank you.

03:06.928 --> 03:08.733
Those aren't burns, are they?

03:10.188 --> 03:12.169
And they all came in
with these initial symptoms?

03:12.319 --> 03:16.145
Localized infections. Ulcerations.
Mostly of cuts and scratches.

03:16.295 --> 03:18.996
You get pretty dinged-up out there,
even in the protective gear.

03:19.146 --> 03:22.123
- Where're you keeping the sick?
- Down at a station house in Benton

03:22.273 --> 03:24.553
- about 5 clicks from here.
- They're all like that?

03:24.804 --> 03:26.208
It gets worse.

03:31.359 --> 03:34.061
Pneumonia,
infection in the lobes of the lungs.

03:34.211 --> 03:36.166
Looks like pulmonary abscesses as well.

03:36.316 --> 03:39.273
Those are a couple days old, from
the first guys who came down with it.

03:39.423 --> 03:40.413
How they doing?

03:40.585 --> 03:43.792
3 have developed septicemia,
19 others are at various stages,

03:43.946 --> 03:45.092
and 2 are dead.

03:45.388 --> 03:47.401
- You're treating them with?
- Mainly antibiotics.

03:47.551 --> 03:49.755
We're having a limited success
with tetracycline.

03:49.905 --> 03:52.146
So what makes you think
it's noncommunicable?

03:52.296 --> 03:54.363
Five firefighters
carried the sick to base camp.

03:54.513 --> 03:55.993
They're not showing any symptoms.

03:56.143 --> 03:58.070
Doesn't make you want
to break into song,

03:58.220 --> 03:59.736
but it's a little ray of sunshine.

03:59.954 --> 04:01.003
Any thoughts?

04:01.195 --> 04:04.123
We'll get some samples back to our lab
and have a look at them.

04:04.273 --> 04:06.290
I appreciate the help, guys.
The wind changes,

04:06.440 --> 04:08.627
we're gonna need
all the healthy bodies we can get.

04:09.062 --> 04:11.419
- How many are out there right now?
- Last count I heard

04:11.569 --> 04:13.033
was close to 600.

04:13.532 --> 04:14.785
<i>Doctor Lowen?</i>

04:15.641 --> 04:16.649
Lowen, go.

04:16.800 --> 04:19.048
<i>We got three more down, Doc.
In transport.</i>

04:20.526 --> 04:22.017
Make that close to 597.

04:24.587 --> 04:28.767
ReGenesis
3x08 <i>Sleepers</i>

04:31.824 --> 04:34.947
Subtitles
Team NorBAC

